rlIPv6.name: rlIPv6
rlIPv6.contactinfo: Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose , CA 95134-1706 USA Website: Cisco Small Business Home http://www.cisco.com/smb>;, Cisco Small Business Support Community <http://www.cisco.com/go/smallbizsupport>
rlIPv6.description: The private MIB module definition for IPv6 MIB.

rlIpAddressTable.name: rlIpAddressTable
rlIpAddressTable.description: This table is parallel to ipAddressTable, and is used to add/delete IPv6 entries to/from that table. It contains private objects.

rlIpAddressEntry.name: rlIpAddressEntry
rlIpAddressEntry.description: An address mapping for a particular interface.

rlIpAddressPrefixLength.name: rlIpAddressPrefixLength
rlIpAddressPrefixLength.description: The prefix length of this address.

rlIpAddressType.name: rlIpAddressType
rlIpAddressType.description: Extend standard field ipAddressType to multicast

rlipv6InterfaceTable.name: rlipv6InterfaceTable
rlipv6InterfaceTable.description: This table is parallel to ipv6InterfaceTable, and is used to configure additional interface parameters.

rlipv6InterfaceEntry.name: rlipv6InterfaceEntry
rlipv6InterfaceEntry.description: Additional configuration parameters for a particular interface.

rlipv6InterfaceNdDadAttemps.name: rlipv6InterfaceNdDadAttemps
rlipv6InterfaceNdDadAttemps.description: ND Duplicated address detection number of attempts.

rlipv6InterfaceAutoconfigEnable.name: rlipv6InterfaceAutoconfigEnable
rlipv6InterfaceAutoconfigEnable.description: Enables or disables Stateless Address Auto configuration on specific interface.

rlipv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachSendEnable.name: rlipv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachSendEnable
rlipv6InterfaceIcmpUnreachSendEnable.description: Enables or disables sending of ICMP Destination Unreachable Error on specific interface.

rlipv6InterfaceLinkMTU.name: rlipv6InterfaceLinkMTU
rlipv6InterfaceLinkMTU.description: The maximum transmission unit (MTU) size of IPv6 packets sent on an interface in bytes.

rlipv6InterfaceMLDVersion.name: rlipv6InterfaceMLDVersion
rlipv6InterfaceMLDVersion.description: Set version of MLD protocol on specific interface.

rlipv6InterfaceRetransmitTime.name: rlipv6InterfaceRetransmitTime
rlipv6InterfaceRetransmitTime.description: This value will be included in all IPv6 router advertisements sent out this interface. Very short intervals are not recommended in normal IPv6 operation. When a nondefault value is configured, the configured time is both advertised and used by the router itself. When value 0 is configured, 0 seconds (unspecified) advertised in router advertisements and the value 1000 milliseconds is used for the neighbor discovery activity of the router itself.

rlipv6InterfaceIcmpRedirectSendEnable.name: rlipv6InterfaceIcmpRedirectSendEnable
rlipv6InterfaceIcmpRedirectSendEnable.description: Enables or disables sending of ICMP IPv6 redirect messages to re-send a packet through the same interface on which the packet was received.

rlinetCidrRouteTable.name: rlinetCidrRouteTable
rlinetCidrRouteTable.description: This table is parallel to inetCidrRouteTable, and is used to configure or display additional route parameters.

rlinetCidrRouteEntry.name: rlinetCidrRouteEntry
rlinetCidrRouteEntry.description: Additional parameters for a particular route.

rlinetCidrRouteLifetime.name: rlinetCidrRouteLifetime
rlinetCidrRouteLifetime.description: The remaining length of time, in seconds, that this route will continue to be valid, i.e., time until deprecation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity.

rlinetCidrRouteInfo.name: rlinetCidrRouteInfo
rlinetCidrRouteInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route, as determined by the value specified in the route's inetCidrRouteProto value.

rlipNetToPhysicalTable.name: rlipNetToPhysicalTable
rlipNetToPhysicalTable.description: This table is parallel to ipNetToPhysicalTable, and is used to configure or display additional neighbor parameters.

rlipNetToPhysicalIsRouter.name: rlipNetToPhysicalIsRouter
rlipNetToPhysicalIsRouter.description: This object has the value 'true(1)', if the neighbor is router; otherwise, the value is 'false(2)'.

rlipNetToPhysicalReachableConfirmed.name: rlipNetToPhysicalReachableConfirmed
rlipNetToPhysicalReachableConfirmed.description: Time (in seconds) since the address was confirmed to be reachable. Only, relevant for dynamic entries.

rlipv6IcmpErrorRatelimitInterval.name: rlipv6IcmpErrorRatelimitInterval
rlipv6IcmpErrorRatelimitInterval.description: The time interval between tokens being placed in the bucket, each token represents a single ICMP error message. The interval measured in milliseconds.

rlipv6IcmpErrorRatelimitBucketSize.name: rlipv6IcmpErrorRatelimitBucketSize
rlipv6IcmpErrorRatelimitBucketSize.description: The maximum number of tokens stored in the bucket, each token represents a single ICMP error message.

rlipv6LLDefaultZone.name: rlipv6LLDefaultZone
rlipv6LLDefaultZone.description: The interface which would be used as the egress interface for packets sent without a specified IPv6Z interface identifier or with the default '0' identifier. Zero value means no default interface specified.

rlIpv6GeneralPrefixTable.name: rlIpv6GeneralPrefixTable
rlIpv6GeneralPrefixTable.description: This table defines general prefix description, based on which a number of longer, more specific, prefixes can be defined.

rlIpv6GeneralPrefixEntry.name: rlIpv6GeneralPrefixEntry
rlIpv6GeneralPrefixEntry.description: Single entry in general prefix table.

rlIpv6GeneralPrefixName.name: rlIpv6GeneralPrefixName
rlIpv6GeneralPrefixName.description: The name assigned to the prefix.

rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddrType.name: rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddrType
rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddrType.description: Prefix inet address type. Has to be IPv6.

rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddr.name: rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddr
rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddr.description: The IPv6 network assigned to the general prefix. This argument must be in the form documented in RFC4293 where the address is specified in hexadecimal using 16-bit values between colons.

rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddrPrefixLength.name: rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddrPrefixLength
rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddrPrefixLength.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits that form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the inet address before being compared to the value in the rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInetAddr field.

rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInterfaceId.name: rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInterfaceId
rlIpv6GeneralPrefixInterfaceId.description: Interface id to use when creating prefix based on point-to-point interface.

rlipv6MaximumHopsNumber.name: rlipv6MaximumHopsNumber
rlipv6MaximumHopsNumber.description: Maximum number of hops used in router advertisements and all IPv6 packets that are originated by the router.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixTable.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixTable
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixTable.description: This table defines IPv6 prefixes which are included in IPv6 Neighbor Discovery (ND) router advertisements.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixEntry.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixEntry
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixEntry.description: Single entry in Neighbor Discovery Prefix table.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixIfIndex.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixIfIndex
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixIfIndex.description: The index value that uniquely identifies the interface on which this prefix is configured. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IF-MIB's ifIndex.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixIsDefault.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixIsDefault
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixIsDefault.description: Indicates whether this object belongs to 'default' entry. Default entry contains specifics about advertising prefixes which were created from local ipv6 addresses.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddrType.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddrType
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddrType.description: Prefix inet address type. Has to be IPv6.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddr.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddr
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddr.description: The IPv6 network prefix to include in router advertisements. This argument must be in the form documented in RFC4293 where the address is specified in hexadecimal using 16-bit values between colons.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddrPrefixLe.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddrPrefixLength
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixInetAddrPrefixLe.description: The length of the IPv6 prefix. A decimal value that indicates how many of the high-order contiguous bits of the address comprise the prefix (the network portion of the address).

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdminStatus.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdminStatus
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdminStatus.description: Admin status of the entry. Relevant only for default entry.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvertise.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvertise
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvertise.description: Whether the prefix is included in router advertisements.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixOnLinkStatus.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixOnLinkStatus
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixOnLinkStatus.description: If object has the value 'onlink(1)', this prefix is confidered as on-link. This prefix will be advertised with the L-bit set and will be present in the Routing Table. If object has the value 'not-onlink(2)', this prefix will be advertised with the L-bit clear, but connected state of the prefix will not be changed. If object has the value 'offlink(3)', this prefix is confidered as on-link. This prefix will be advertised with the L-bit clear, and will be not present in the Routing Table.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAutonomousFlag.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAutonomousFlag
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAutonomousFlag.description: If object has the value 'true(1)', this prefix indicates to hosts on the local link that the specified prefix can be used for IPv6 autoconfiguration. The prefix will be advertised with the A-bit set.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvPreferredLife.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvPreferredLifetime
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvPreferredLife.description: The amount of time (in seconds) that the specified IPv6 prefix is advertised as being preferred.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvValidLifetime.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvValidLifetime
rlIpv6RouterAdvertPrefixAdvValidLifetime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) that the specified IPv6 prefix is advertised as being valid.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertTable.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertTable
rlIpv6RouterAdvertTable.description: This table is parallel to inetCidrRouteTable, and is used to configure or display additional route parameters.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertEntry.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertEntry
rlIpv6RouterAdvertEntry.description: Additional parameters for a particular route.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertAdvIntervalOption.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertAdvIntervalOption
rlIpv6RouterAdvertAdvIntervalOption.description: Indicates to a visiting mobile node the interval at which that node may expect to receive RAs. The node may use this information in its movement detection algorithm.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertRouterPreference.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertRouterPreference
rlIpv6RouterAdvertRouterPreference.description: Configures a default router preference (DRP) for the router on a specific interface.

rlIpv6RouterAdvertIsCurHopLimitUserConfi.name: rlIpv6RouterAdvertIsCurHopLimitUserConfigured
rlIpv6RouterAdvertIsCurHopLimitUserConfi.description: Indicates that hop limit value used in router advertisement is an user configured value and not necessarily value that is used by router itself.

rlipv6InetCidrTableClear.name: rlipv6InetCidrTableClear
rlipv6InetCidrTableClear.description: This scalar indicates to clear all ipv6 routes from inetCidrTable.

rlIpv6PathMtuTable.name: rlIpv6PathMtuTable
rlIpv6PathMtuTable.description: This table used to represent all Path MTU changes to specific destination received from 'packet-too-big' messages.

rlIpv6PathMtuEntry.name: rlIpv6PathMtuEntry
rlIpv6PathMtuEntry.description: Single entry in Path MTU table.

rlIpv6PathMtuEntryInetDestAddrType.name: rlIpv6PathMtuEntryInetDestAddrType
rlIpv6PathMtuEntryInetDestAddrType.description: Prefix inet address type. Has to be IPv6.

rlIpv6PathMtuEntryInetDestAddr.name: rlIpv6PathMtuEntryInetDestAddr
rlIpv6PathMtuEntryInetDestAddr.description: The IPv6 destination address for which packet-too-big message was received. This argument must be in the form documented in RFC4293 where the address is specified in hexadecimal using 16-bit values between colons.

rlIpv6PathMtuEntryMtu.name: rlIpv6PathMtuEntryMtu
rlIpv6PathMtuEntryMtu.description: The MTU value that was received in packet-too-bug message for specific destination.

rlInetStaticRouteTable.name: rlInetStaticRouteTable
rlInetStaticRouteTable.description: This entity's static (user configured) Inet Routing table. Entries are MAX-ACCESSible even if not used for forwarding

rlInetStaticRouteEntry.name: rlInetStaticRouteEntry
rlInetStaticRouteEntry.description: A particular Static(user configured) route to a particular destination.

rlInetStaticRouteDestType.name: rlInetStaticRouteDestType
rlInetStaticRouteDestType.description: The type of the address used as the destination internetwork address or subnet address.

rlInetStaticRouteDest.name: rlInetStaticRouteDest
rlInetStaticRouteDest.description: Destination internetwork address or subnet address. The destination prefix length is applied to this value, and to a particular destination address, to determine whether the route applies to the particular address. If the prefix length is L, then applying the length to an address means taking the first L bits of the address.

rlInetStaticRoutePfxLen.name: rlInetStaticRoutePfxLen
rlInetStaticRoutePfxLen.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits that form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the rlInetStaticRouteDest field.

rlInetStaticRouteNextHopType.name: rlInetStaticRouteNextHopType
rlInetStaticRouteNextHopType.description: The type of the address used as the next-hop address for this route.

rlInetStaticRouteNextHop.name: rlInetStaticRouteNextHop
rlInetStaticRouteNextHop.description: The next-hop IP address, if any. If rlInetStaticRouteAction is 'forward', there may or may not be a next-hop IP address. A next-hop IP address is not required if an output interface index is specified (in other words, if rlInetStaticRouteIfIndex is non-zero). If rlInetStaticRouteAction is not 'forward', there is no next-hop IP address. If there is no next-hop IP address, the rlInetStaticRouteNextHop object is set to all zeroes.

rlInetStaticRouteIfIndex.name: rlInetStaticRouteIfIndex
rlInetStaticRouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value that identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. A value of 0 is valid and represents the scenario where no interface is specified.

rlInetStaticRoutePathCost.name: rlInetStaticRoutePathCost
rlInetStaticRoutePathCost.description: Path cost for this static route.

rlInetStaticRouteType.name: rlInetStaticRouteType
rlInetStaticRouteType.description: Same as inetCidrRouteType MIB (excluded 'other' route type)

rlInetStaticRouteOwner.name: rlInetStaticRouteOwner
rlInetStaticRouteOwner.description: Static - The route is configured over Static IP. This route is written to configuration files. Dhcp - The route is Configured by DHCP (received as part of DHCP configuration) This route IS NOT written to configuration files Default - The route is Configured by default system config exists till any other configuration is applied. Icmp - The route is Configured by ICMP protocol either by router advertisements or to be advertised in router advertisements .

rlInetStaticRouteRowStatus.name: rlInetStaticRouteRowStatus
rlInetStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions. A row entry cannot be modified when the status is marked as active(1).

rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearTable.name: rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearTable
rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearTable.description: This entity is used to clear all or specific-type entries from ipNetToPhysicalTable.

rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearEntry.name: rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearEntry
rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearEntry.description: A particular entry in this table.

rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearIfIndex.name: rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearIfIndex
rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearIfIndex.description: Interface index of to clear or zero in case of whole table.

rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearScope.name: rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearScope
rlIpNetToPhysicalTableClearScope.description: Scope of the action - type of entries to delete.

rlInetRoutingDistanceTable.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceTable
rlInetRoutingDistanceTable.description: This table defines administrative distances for different protocol routes that are inserted into the routing table.

rlInetRoutingDistanceEntry.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceEntry
rlInetRoutingDistanceEntry.description: A set of distances per inet address type.

rlInetRoutingDistanceType.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceType
rlInetRoutingDistanceType.description: The inet address type for distance definitions set, either IPv4 or IPv6.

rlInetRoutingDistanceConnected.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceConnected
rlInetRoutingDistanceConnected.description: The administrative distance used for directly connected routes.

rlInetRoutingDistanceStatic.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceStatic
rlInetRoutingDistanceStatic.description: The administrative distance used for static routes.

rlInetRoutingDistanceRip.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceRip
rlInetRoutingDistanceRip.description: The administrative distance used for RIP routes.

rlInetRoutingDistanceOspfInternal.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceOspfInternal
rlInetRoutingDistanceOspfInternal.description: The administrative distance used for OSPF internal routes.

rlInetRoutingDistanceOspfExternal.name: rlInetRoutingDistanceOspfExternal
rlInetRoutingDistanceOspfExternal.description: The administrative distance used for OSPF Autonomous System external routes.

rlInternInetCidrRouteTable.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteTable
rlInternInetCidrRouteTable.description: Internal inetCidrRouteTable - this entity's IP Routing table.

rlInternInetCidrRouteEntry.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteEntry
rlInternInetCidrRouteEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy (as reflected in the rlInternInetCidrRoutePolicy object). Dynamically created rows will survive an agent reboot. Implementers need to be aware that if the total number of elements (octets or sub-identifiers) in rlInternInetCidrRouteDest, rlInternInetCidrRoutePolicy, and rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHop exceeds 111, then OIDs of column instances in this table will have more than 128 sub- identifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c, or SNMPv3.

rlInternInetCidrRouteDestType.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteDestType
rlInternInetCidrRouteDestType.description: The type of the rlInternInetCidrRouteDest address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

rlInternInetCidrRouteDest.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteDest
rlInternInetCidrRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. The type of this address is determined by the value of the rlInternInetCidrRouteDestType object. The values for the index objects rlInternInetCidrRouteDest and rlInternInetCidrRoutePfxLen must be consistent. When the value of rlInternInetCidrRouteDest (excluding the zone index, if one is present) is x, then the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the mask formed from the corresponding index object rlInternInetCidrRoutePfxLen MUST be equal to x. If not, then the index pair is not consistent and an inconsistentName error must be returned on SET or CREATE requests.

rlInternInetCidrRoutePfxLen.name: rlInternInetCidrRoutePfxLen
rlInternInetCidrRoutePfxLen.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits that form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the rlInternInetCidrRouteDest field. The values for the index objects rlInternInetCidrRouteDest and rlInternInetCidrRoutePfxLen must be consistent. When the value of rlInternInetCidrRouteDest (excluding the zone index, if one is present) is x, then the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the mask formed from the corresponding index object rlInternInetCidrRoutePfxLen MUST be equal to x. If not, then the index pair is not consistent and an inconsistentName error must be returned on SET or CREATE requests.

rlInternInetCidrRoutePolicy.name: rlInternInetCidrRoutePolicy
rlInternInetCidrRoutePolicy.description: This object is an opaque object without any defined semantics. Its purpose is to serve as an additional index that may delineate between multiple entries to the same destination. The value { 0 0 } shall be used as the default value for this object.

rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHopType.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHopType
rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHopType.description: The type of the rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Value should be set to unknown(0) for non-remote routes. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHop.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHop
rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next system en route. For non-remote routes, a zero length string. The type of this address is determined by the value of the rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHopType object.

rlInternInetCidrRouteIfIndex.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteIfIndex
rlInternInetCidrRouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value that identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. A value of 0 is valid and represents the scenario where no interface is specified.

rlInternInetCidrRouteType.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteType
rlInternInetCidrRouteType.description: The type of route. Note that local(3) refers to a route for which the next hop is the final destination; remote(4) refers to a route for which the next hop is not the final destination. Routes that do not result in traffic forwarding or rejection should not be displayed, even if the implementation keeps them stored internally. reject(2) refers to a route that, if matched, discards the message as unreachable and returns a notification (e.g., ICMP error) to the message sender. This is used in some protocols as a means of correctly aggregating routes. blackhole(5) refers to a route that, if matched, discards the message silently.

rlInternInetCidrRouteProto.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteProto
rlInternInetCidrRouteProto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.

rlInternInetCidrRouteAge.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteAge
rlInternInetCidrRouteAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of 'too old' can be implied, except through knowledge of the routing protocol by which the route was learned.

rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHopAS.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHopAS
rlInternInetCidrRouteNextHopAS.description: The Autonomous System Number of the Next Hop. The semantics of this object are determined by the routing- protocol specified in the route's rlInternInetCidrRouteProto value. When this object is unknown or not relevant, its value should be set to zero.

rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric1.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric1
rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing- protocol specified in the route's rlInternInetCidrRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric2.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric2
rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric2.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing- protocol specified in the route's rlInternInetCidrRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric3.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric3
rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric3.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing- protocol specified in the route's rlInternInetCidrRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric4.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric4
rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric4.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing- protocol specified in the route's rlInternInetCidrRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric5.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric5
rlInternInetCidrRouteMetric5.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing- protocol specified in the route's rlInternInetCidrRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

rlInternInetCidrRouteStatus.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteStatus
rlInternInetCidrRouteStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions. A row entry cannot be modified when the status is marked as active(1).

rlInternInetCidrRouteLifetime.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteLifetime
rlInternInetCidrRouteLifetime.description: The remaining length of time, in seconds, that this route will continue to be valid, i.e., time until deprecation. A value of 4,294,967,295 represents infinity.

rlInternInetCidrRouteInfo.name: rlInternInetCidrRouteInfo
rlInternInetCidrRouteInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route, as determined by the value specified in the route's inetCidrRouteProto value.

rlInternInetStaticRouteTable.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteTable
rlInternInetStaticRouteTable.description: This entity's static (user configured) Inet Routing table. Entries are MAX-ACCESSible even if not used for forwarding

rlInternInetStaticRouteEntry.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteEntry
rlInternInetStaticRouteEntry.description: A particular Static(user configured) route to a particular destination.

rlInternInetStaticRouteDestType.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteDestType
rlInternInetStaticRouteDestType.description: The type of the address used as the destination internetwork address or subnet address.

rlInternInetStaticRouteDest.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteDest
rlInternInetStaticRouteDest.description: Destination internetwork address or subnet address. The destination prefix length is applied to this value, and to a particular destination address, to determine whether the route applies to the particular address. If the prefix length is L, then applying the length to an address means taking the first L bits of the address.

rlInternInetStaticRoutePfxLen.name: rlInternInetStaticRoutePfxLen
rlInternInetStaticRoutePfxLen.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits that form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the rlInternInetStaticRouteDest field.

rlInternInetStaticRouteNextHopType.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteNextHopType
rlInternInetStaticRouteNextHopType.description: The type of the address used as the next-hop address for this route.

rlInternInetStaticRouteNextHop.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteNextHop
rlInternInetStaticRouteNextHop.description: The next-hop IP address, if any. If rlInternInetStaticRouteAction is 'forward', there may or may not be a next-hop IP address. A next-hop IP address is not required if an output interface index is specified (in other words, if rlInternInetStaticRouteIfIndex is non-zero). If rlInternInetStaticRouteAction is not 'forward', there is no next-hop IP address. If there is no next-hop IP address, the rlInternInetStaticRouteNextHop object is set to all zeroes.

rlInternInetStaticRouteIfIndex.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteIfIndex
rlInternInetStaticRouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value that identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. A value of 0 is valid and represents the scenario where no interface is specified.

rlInternInetStaticRoutePathCost.name: rlInternInetStaticRoutePathCost
rlInternInetStaticRoutePathCost.description: Path cost for this static route.

rlInternInetStaticRouteType.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteType
rlInternInetStaticRouteType.description: Same as inetCidrRouteType MIB (excluded 'other' route type)

rlInternInetStaticRouteOwner.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteOwner
rlInternInetStaticRouteOwner.description: Static - The route is configured over Static IP. This route is written to configuration files. Dhcp - The route is Configured by DHCP (received as part of DHCP configuration) This route IS NOT written to configuration files Default - The route is Configured by default system config exists till any other configuration is applied. Icmp - The route is Configured by ICMP protocol either by router advertisements or to be advertised in router advertisements .

rlInternInetStaticRouteRowStatus.name: rlInternInetStaticRouteRowStatus
rlInternInetStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions. A row entry cannot be modified when the status is marked as active(1).

rlIpv6HostForwardingTable.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingTable
rlIpv6HostForwardingTable.description: This entity's IPv6 host forwarding table.

rlIpv6HostForwardingEntry.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingEntry
rlIpv6HostForwardingEntry.description: A particular Static(user configured) route to a particular destination.

rlIpv6HostForwardingDestType.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingDestType
rlIpv6HostForwardingDestType.description: The type of the address used as the destination internetwork address or subnet address.

rlIpv6HostForwardingDest.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingDest
rlIpv6HostForwardingDest.description: Destination internetwork address or subnet address.

rlIpv6HostForwardingPfxLen.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingPfxLen
rlIpv6HostForwardingPfxLen.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits that form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the rlIpv6HostForwardingDest field.

rlIpv6HostForwardingNextHopType.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingNextHopType
rlIpv6HostForwardingNextHopType.description: The type of the address used as the next-hop address for this route.

rlIpv6HostForwardingNextHop.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingNextHop
rlIpv6HostForwardingNextHop.description: The next-hop IP address, if any. A next-hop IP address is not required if an output interface index is specified (in other words, if rlIpv6HostForwardingIfIndex is non-zero). If there is no next-hop IP address, the rlIpv6HostForwardingNextHop object is set to all zeroes.

rlIpv6HostForwardingIfIndex.name: rlIpv6HostForwardingIfIndex
rlIpv6HostForwardingIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value that identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. A value of 0 is valid and represents the scenario where no interface is specified.

rlipv6EnabledByDefaultRemovedIfindex.name: rlipv6EnabledByDefaultRemovedIfindex
rlipv6EnabledByDefaultRemovedIfindex.description: the MIB is relevant when mtsc parameter DHCPv6_client_enabled_by_default is TRUE. If the MIB has non zero value the meaning is that ipv6 interface has removed from configuration by the user on the interface and signs to application not to add ipv6 interface. Otherwise (zero value) - the meaning is that Ipv6 interface must be added.

rlManagementIpv6.name: rlManagementIpv6
rlManagementIpv6.description: The system management IPv6 address which is kept between system mode changes

rlManagementIpv6Action.name: rlManagementIpv6Action
rlManagementIpv6Action.description: The system management IPv6 action: clear - delete all ipv6 interfaces from startup configuration database except rlManagementIpv6
